# SDD Core Rules

## Four Pillars

- **Traceability**: every behavior and test must cite `@req SCD-XXX-NNN`.
- **DRY**: types defined once in `lib/api/types.ts`; logic in `lib/coverage.ts`. Import, never duplicate.
- **Deterministic Enforcement**: `pnpm verify` = typecheck + lint + test + check-coverage + build. Must stay green.
- **Parsimony**: no unjustified deps, no boilerplate comments, no over-abstraction.

## Traceability — `@req` annotation

```ts
// @req SCD-FLT-001
export function filterRequirements(reqs: Requirement[], f: Filter) { ... }
```

Every public behavior in `lib/`, `app/`, `components/` needs one. Every test file first line.

## No `any`

```ts
// ❌ BAD
function parse(data: any) { ... }

// ✅ GOOD
function parse(data: unknown): Result<Stats, ApiError> { ... }
```

## No Duplicated Types / Logic

```ts
// ❌ BAD — redefining a type already in lib/api/types.ts
type Requirement = { id: string; status: string };

// ✅ GOOD
import type { Requirement } from '@/lib/api/types';
```

## Commit Format

```
feat(table): URL-synced filters [SCD-FLT-002]
fix(api): handle malformed JSON response [SCD-API-003]
```

Pattern: `type(scope): message [SCD-XXX-NNN]`
